  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    Assets
    The Assets class represents a collection of fonts, colors, and images used in the application.
    ClientWaiting
    The ClientWaiting class represents a JPanel that displays a waiting screen for the client, indicating that it is waiting for the host to start the game.
    GameOver
    The GameOver class represents a JPanel that displays the game over screen.
    GameScreen
    The `GameScreen` class represents the game screen panel in the application.
    JoinIP
    The JoinIP class represents a JPanel used for joining a specific IP address.
    MainScreen
    The MainScreen class represents the main panel of the application.
    ServerLobby
    The ServerLobby class represents a JPanel that displays the server lobby interface.
    ThemeActions
    The ThemeActions class represents a utility class for handling theme data.
    ThemeSelect
    The ThemeSelect class represents a JPanel that allows the user to select a theme.
